      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "traybake",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpa6f53x00002sv4z9staww8"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " is the simplest form of cake. One bowl, one tin, no layers to level and sandwich. The desiccated coconut keeps this one moist for days; the lime drizzle applied hot is the other reason it stays good. The lime zest in the batter fades slightly in the oven, which is why the drizzle matters.",
            "type": "text"
          }
