      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix, bake, drizzle, 25 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C fan. Grease and line a 30 × 20 cm baking tin with baking paper. Beat the softened {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} (cake amount) until pale and fluffy. Beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time. Fold in the {{self-raising-flour}}, {{desiccated-coconut}} (cake amount), {{lime}} zest, and {{whole-milk}}. Spread into the prepared tin and level the surface.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 23 to 25 minutes, until well-risen, golden, and a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean. While the cake bakes, stir together the {{lime}} juice and {{caster-sugar}} (drizzle amount). The moment the cake comes out of the oven, poke holes across the surface with a skewer and pour over the drizzle. Scatter with {{desiccated-coconut}} if using. Leave in the tin until completely cool, then cut into squares.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
